# LP STL iterative preview workflow

When changing anything that affects the 3D model (`generate_wyndor_stl.py`, constants, labels, contours, accents, or `preview.py`), **always finish by running the iterative preview**. Each iteration must produce **both**:

1. A fresh **`output/preview.png`** (three-view static image for Cursor/Finder)
2. A fresh **rotatable pyglet window** (drag to rotate, scroll to zoom)

Do not only tell John to run it — run it yourself after every change.

## What to run

From `wyndor_print/`, run `preview.py --interactive`. It regenerates STLs by default, **always writes a new `output/preview.png`**, then opens the interactive viewer.

```bash
cd "/Users/johnb/Documents/Cursor Files/3D Printing/wyndor_print" && MPLCONFIGDIR="/Users/johnb/Documents/Cursor Files/3D Printing/wyndor_print/.mplconfig" .venv/bin/python preview.py --interactive
```

- **Agent runs this** after every iterative mesh/geometry edit (background, `required_permissions: ["all"]`).
- Wait for `Saved preview image: .../output/preview.png` in output — that confirms the PNG was regenerated.
- Do not skip the PNG step; `preview.py` writes it on every run (even without `--interactive`).
- Use `--no-regenerate` only when re-viewing existing STLs with no generator changes.

## Dependencies

If interactive preview fails, ensure pyglet 1.x is installed:

```bash
cd "/Users/johnb/Documents/Cursor Files/3D Printing/wyndor_print" && .venv/bin/pip install "pyglet<2"
```

## Project layout

| File | Role |
|---|---|
| `generate_wyndor_stl.py` | Mesh generator → `output/wyndor_body.stl` + `output/wyndor_accents.stl` |
| `preview.py` | Regenerate (default) + static PNG + optional interactive window |
| `output/preview.png` | Three-view static snapshot for quick checks in Cursor |

## Model conventions (Wyndor)

- **Body** (filament 1): feasible-region solid with sloped objective top.
- **Accents** (filament 2): top iso-profit contour lines + etched labels; side-wall constraint labels (no vertical edge ridges).

Tweak geometry via constants at the top of `generate_wyndor_stl.py` (`CONTOUR_LEVELS`, `TEXT_FONT_SIZE`, `WALL_LABEL_V_FRACTION`, etc.).
